cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.AR, cs.CE

This paper discusses the efficient deployment of IoT over cellular networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication protocols. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes an analytical model to calculate energy consumption, which falls under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of optimization techniques and Markov chains suggests that the paper could also be classified under cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.AR (Hardware Architecture). Finally, the paper discusses the practical implications of the proposed optimizations, which could be relevant to the category of cs.CE (Computers and Society).
